In 1967, US 410 was dropped from the U.S. Highway System, and became US 12, except from Elma to Naches. From Elma to Mud Bay, SR 410 was renumbered SR 8. From Mud Bay to Tacoma, the designation was removed from concurrencies with US 101 and I-5/US 99 (this section is skipped in this list). From Tacoma to Naches, the highway remained numbered SR 410. In 1973, the section of SR 410 from Tacoma to Sumner was renumbered as a portion of SR 167.
